cs.MM, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR 

The paper proposes a deep learning approach for recognizing the interestingness of video content and a Deep Q-Network (DQN) approach for rate adaptation by incorporating video interestingness information. This involves analyzing the semantic information of the video content, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) categories. The use of deep learning and DQN also suggests that the paper may fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and information retrieval (cs.IR) categories.
